Johann Balthasar König (baptised 28 January 1691 – buried 2 April 1758) was a German Baroque composer, especially of hymn melodies, having published a hymnal with 1,913 melodies.
König married in 1717 Anna Maria Pfaff, the daughter of a tailor.
Telemann became the godfather of their son Georg Philipp, born in 1718.
He was promoted to municipal Kapellmeister (director of music) in 1727, succeeding Johann Christoph Bodinus (1690–1727).
He was promoted to municipal Kapellmeister (director of music) in 1727, succeeding Johann Christoph Bodinus (1690–1727).
His most important work is the 1738 collection Harmonischer Liederschatz, with 1,913 melodies, of which 358 were not published before.
